headlines.description: — Tyler Herro had 27 points and eight rebounds to help the Miami Heat beat the Utah Jazz 111-105 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyler Herro scores 27 points, Heat hold off Jazz 111-105

headlines.description: — For Indiana Pacers coach Rick Carlisle, Justin Holiday is a nice luxury to have in the second unit.

— Spencer Dinwiddie scored 23 points, Montrezl Harrell added 20 and the Washington Wizards used a 20-0 first-half run to defeat the Orlando Magic 104-92 on Saturday night for their fourth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dinwiddie, Harrell lead Wizards to their fourth straight win

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Nickeil Alexander-Walker scored 21 points, Brandon Ingram returned from a seven-game absence to add 19 and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Memphis Grizzlies 112-101 on Saturday night to snap a nine-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans beat Grizzlies 112-101 to snap 9-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored 14 of his 24 points in the fourth quarter, Isaiah Stewart scored 20 and Detroit used a big finish to beat short-handed Toronto 127-121 on Saturday night, the Pistons’ fourth straight victory over the Raptors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jerami Grant scores 24 points, Pistons beat Raptors 127-121

headlines.description: — Darius Garland made two free throws with 9.4 seconds left and the Cleveland Cavaliers rallied from 19 points down in the third quarter to stun the Boston Celtics 91-89 on Saturday night in the opener of a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland, Cavs erase 19-point deficit to beat Celtics 91-89

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Clippers shut down Karl-Anthony Towns, and the Minnesota Timberwolves disappeared with him.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rout Wolves 129-102 for 7th straight victory
